      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_MeterBilling_Retrieve",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve records from the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Billing.MeterBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table based on various input parameters. It allows for flexible querying by accepting multiple optional parameters, which can be used to filter the results based on specific criteria such as billing period, account utility company, energy source, original account number, original meter number, or a specific meter billing sequence ID."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is relatively straightforward, with a simple conditional logic structure that determines which query to execute based on the presence and values of the input parameters. It primarily involves basic SQL SELECT statements with conditional WHERE clauses."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
